OL,3,CFinancial worries put medieval
OL,4,CCumbrian fair at risk
OL,6,FIn fact, it was performing so well
OL,7,Fthat during the pandemic, when the
OL,8,Fevent was cancelled for two years in a
OL,9,Frow, organisers were able to donate
OL,10,Fmoney to local charities.
OL,12,FBut in 2022, following the death of
OL,13,Fthe Queen, the fair was cancelled
OL,14,Fagain. This was unprecedented and it
OL,15,Fmeant that deposits and money that had
OL,16,Falready been paid out could not be
OL,17,Frecovered.
